-- Portugal Hotel Revenue Drops 6.8% in April From Year Earlier
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-06-15T10:07:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/portugal-hotel-revenue-drops-6-8-in-april-from-year-earlier.html
Portugal ’s hotels recorded a 6.8
percent drop in revenue in April from the same month last year
as overnight stays by Portuguese tourists declined.  Revenue fell to 143.3 million euros ($181 million) in
April, the Lisbon-based National Statistics Institute said today
in an e-mailed statement. In the first four months, revenue
dropped 4.1 percent to 411.4 million euros.  Tourism represents about a tenth of Portugal’s gross
domestic product, according to the  Economy Ministry .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
